== 制作 ==
影片于洛杉矶拍摄，采用精美的布景及计算机动画渲染的3500张来自中国的静态照片及2分钟画面。为了塑造真实感，多位北京的演员凭签证前来美国参与拍摄。法庭和监狱场景按照中国律师及法官的描述重塑，中国囚犯被处决的画面也是真实的。向艾弗耐特和他的剧组提供影片和描述的人士冒了很大的风险<ref name="dvd">{{cite video|people=Jon Avnet (Director)|title=Red Corner]|medium=DVD|publisher=MGM|location=Los Angeles|date=1997|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0119994/|access-date=2021-04-08|archive-date=2021-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412015359/https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0119994/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 评价 ==
[[烂番茄|烂番茄]]收录23条评论，打出30%的腐烂度<ref name="tomatoes">{{cite web |title=Red Corner (1997) |website=Rotten Tomatoes |url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/red_corner/ |access-date=2020-04-01 |archive-date=2021-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210117035632/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/red_corner |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的{{tsl|en|Janet Maslin|珍妮特·马斯林}}提到了希区柯克式的设定给“定罪”（conviction）一词赋予了双重含义，融合了外界对中国的好奇及娱乐价值<ref>{{cite news |last1=Maslin |first1=Janet |title=FILM REVIEW; Lady Killer? Beijing Is Not Charmed |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/10/31/movies/film-review-lady-killer-beijing-is-not-charmed.html |access-date=2021-03-08 |work=The New York Times |date=1997-10-31 |archive-date=2020-10-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201004024137/https://www.nytimes.com/1997/10/31/movies/film-review-lady-killer-beijing-is-not-charmed.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[芝加哥太阳报|芝加哥太阳报]]》影评人[[罗杰·伊伯特|罗杰·伊伯特]]认为影片是一部“造作累赘的惊悚片，非常彻底地宣泄出理查·基尔不满共产中国的情绪，剧情和角色都笼罩在阴谋中。中国的电影做得都比他们好。有别于《[[蓝风筝|蓝风筝]]》和《[[活着_(电影)|活着]]》等中国电影用局内人的了解和细节批评中国，《红角落》像是一场混搭了[[派瑞·梅森|派瑞·梅森]]的排外游记<ref name="rogerebert">{{cite news |last=Ebert |first=Roger |title=Red Corner |author-link=Roger Ebert |newspaper=Chicago Sun-Times |date=1997-10-31 |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/red-corner-1997 |access-date=2012-03-20 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127032240/https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/red-corner-1997 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

《{{tsl|en|Film Journal International|国际电影杂志}}》的辛西娅·兰斯顿（Cynthia Langston）认为影片“太假、太造作、太明显的好莱坞风，吉尔可能没想让观众增进对相关问题的了解，或是提供相应的解决方案<ref>[http://www.filmjournal.com/filmjournal/search/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1000698469 Red Corner. ''Film Journal International''.]</ref>。”

《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》的肯尼斯·杜兰（Kenneth Turan）认为影片是一部“呆滞乏味的情景剧，某些要紧地方产生的错觉进一步阻碍了剧情的发展。不过这种一己之力对抗体制的故事有点骇人，想要展现中国的司法状况，但却被仇外的态度所拖累<ref name="latimes">{{cite news |last=Turan |first=Kenneth |title='Corner': A Heavy-Handed Battle With Justice in China |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |date=1997-10-31 |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1997/oct/31/entertainment/ca-48484 |access-date=2012-03-20 |archive-date=2015-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151018083334/http://articles.latimes.com/1997/oct/31/entertainment/ca-48484 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

《Salon》影评人安德鲁·奥赫希尔 （Andrew O'Hehir）认为影片的潜台词“吞噬了剧情，留下来的只有基尔的高尚情操及过人的男子气概，两者很明显都受到招待不够的中国女性观众认可。”他认为影片加深了西方世界对亚洲女性性欲的刻板印象（例如《[[苏丝黄的世界|苏丝黄的世界]]》）及过时的刻板印象<ref name="salon">{{cite news |last=O'Hehir |first=Andrew |title=Richard Gere Seduces China |work=Salon |date=1997-10-31 |url=http://www1.salon.com/ent/movies/1997/10/31red.html |access-date=2012-03-20 |archive-date=2009-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090818145513/http://www.salon.com/ent/movies/1997/10/31red.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

Total Film给出3/5星的评分，认为影片是“一部半惊人的惊悚片，在路人导演及无趣的理查·基尔带动下变得黯然失色。尽管如此，新人白灵及不眨眼凝视严苛的中国法律体制不让影片成为一起容易解决的案子”，认为部分描绘中国法律体制待人严苛的戏份“发人深省”，其余场景“娱乐性一般”<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/lady_in_red/|title=Lady in Red|date=2008-04-18|website=Gamesradar|access-date=2021-04-08|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112043042/https://www.gamesradar.com/lady_in_red/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 审查 ==
影片因贬损中国司法体制的形象，在[[中华人民共和国被禁影视作品列表|中国遭到审查]]。吉尔认为影片提供了“看待西藏问题的另一个角度”，尽管没有提到西藏<ref>{{cite news |last1=Guthmann |first1=Edward |title=Gere's 'Corner' on Saving Tibet / Actor's new movie focuses on China and injustices he's been crusading against for years |url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/entertainment/article/Gere-s-Corner-on-Saving-Tibet-Actor-s-new-2824364.php |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=San Francisco Chronicle |date=1997-10-26}}</ref>。中国政府曾派员与制片发行方[[米高梅|米高梅]]公司接洽，询问对方为什么要选择中国国家主席[[江泽民|江泽民]]访问美国期间上映这部电影<ref>{{cite news |last1=Orwall |first1=Bruce |title=MGM Clashes With Richard Gere Over Politics of 'Red Corner' Film |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB878507489110743500 |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=Wall Street journal |date=1997-11-03}}</ref> 。中国[[国家广播电视总局|国家广播电视总局]]向[[美国电影协会|美国电影协会]]主席{{tsl|en|Jack Valenti|杰克·瓦伦蒂}}发去备忘录，并致信中国各大电影公司，要求不得与制作《红角落》的米高梅/联美、《[[達賴的一生|達賴的一生]]》的华特迪士尼及《[[西藏七年_(电影)|西藏七年]]》的哥伦比亚合作，认为上述影片“恶意攻击中国，[[伤害中国人民的感情|伤害中国人民的感情]]”<ref>{{cite news |last1=Waxman |first1=Sharon |title=China Bans Work With Film Studios |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1997/11/01/china-bans-work-with-film-studios/9f3a23e3-4d83-4749-898c-bd1fef276f03/ |access-date=2021-03-08 |work=The Washington Post |date=1997-11-01 |archive-date=2018-06-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612142348/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1997/11/01/china-bans-work-with-film-studios/9f3a23e3-4d83-4749-898c-bd1fef276f03/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。吉尔认为自己积极参与西藏事务，与西藏精神领袖[[第十四世达赖喇嘛|达赖喇嘛]]的关系干扰到他的电影生涯，所参与电影的融资、制作和发行均受到影响<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siegel |first1=Tatiana |title=Richard Gere's Studio Exile: Why His Hollywood Career Took an Indie Turn |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/richard-geres-studio-exile-why-his-hollywood-career-took-an-indie-turn-992258 |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2017-04-18 |archive-date=2019-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925092241/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/features/richard-geres-studio-exile-why-his-hollywood-career-took-an-indie-turn-992258 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Miller |first1=Julie |title=Richard Gere Has a Theory About Why Mainstream Hollywood Dumped Him |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/richard-gere-hollywood-china |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=Vanity Fair |date=2017-04-18 |archive-date=2021-01-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120080612/https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2017/04/richard-gere-hollywood-china |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2020年，吉尔在{{tsl|en|United States Senate Committee on Finance|美国参议院金融委员会}}及国际贸易、海关和全球竞争力小组委员会就“审查制度成为[[非关税壁垒|非关税壁垒]]”作证，认为经济利益迫使电影公司力避提及好莱坞曾提及的社会及政治议题：“想想[[马丁·斯科塞斯|马丁·斯科塞斯]]讲述达赖喇嘛一生的《達賴的一生》，想想我自己那部严厉批评中国司法体制的《红角落》。如果这两部电影放在今天制作，那完全不可能<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siegel |first1=Tatiana |title=Hollywood Is "Increasingly Normalizing" Self-Censorship for China, Report Finds |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-is-increasingly-normalizing-censorship-china-report-finds-1305935 |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=The Hollywood Reporter |date=2020-08-05 |archive-date=2021-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127002420/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-is-increasingly-normalizing-censorship-china-report-finds-1305935 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bunch |first1=Sonny |title=China is turning American movies into propaganda. Enough is enough. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/08/20/china-is-turning-american-movies-into-propaganda-enough-is-enough/ |access-date=2021-03-08 |work=The Washington Post |date=2020-08-20 |archive-date=2021-02-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210212133737/https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/08/20/china-is-turning-american-movies-into-propaganda-enough-is-enough/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Trade and Online Censorship Challenges |url=https://www.c-span.org/video/?473509-1/trade-online-censorship-challenges |access-date=2021-03-08 |publisher=CSpan |date=2020-06-20 |archive-date=2021-03-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307235139/https://www.c-span.org/video/?473509-1%2Ftrade-online-censorship-challenges |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

